@tatatodd following is the list of files in my /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/tensorflow/models/rnn/

/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/tensorflow/models/rnn/
├── init.py
├── init.pyc
├── linear.py
├── linear.pyc
├── rnn_cell.py
├── rnn_cell.pyc
├── rnn.py
├── rnn.pyc
├── seq2seq.py
└── seq2seq.pyc

0 directories, 10 files

By default, on a new terminal environment on my ubuntu 16.04, PYTHONPATH is empty.
I tried setting export PYTHONPATH = /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/tensorflow/:$PYTHONPATH
and
export PYTHONPATH = /path/to/mysoruces/tensorflow/:$PYTHONPATH, where tensorflow is my sources directory head.

I am guessing that this might be problem with tensorflow binary release which I have downloaded from
https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r0.10/get_started/os_setup.html#test-the-tensorflow-installation

And my machine does not have a GPU so I downloaded a non-GPU version of tensorflow using following commands,

export TF_BINARY_URL=https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/linux/cpu/tensorflow-0.10.0-cp27-none-linux_x86_64.whl
sudo pip install --upgrade $TF_BINARY_URL

There is one more thing which I tried, I installed tensorflow through virtual environment and still the problem persists.
